  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.2,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "- [David] Ah, wordsmiths."
      },
      {
        "start": 1.4,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "Welcome to my shop."
      },
      {
        "start": 2.9,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "Here I offer only curiosities."
      },
      {
        "start": 5.5,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "Would you like to see?"
      },
      {
        "start": 6.6,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "Oh, I hoped you might."
      },
      {
        "start": 8.0,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "The words on offer today\nare ingenious, experience,"
      },
      {
        "start": 12.0,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "and evaluate."
      },
      {
        "start": 13.7,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "We'll go through their\ndefinitions, explain their origins,"
      },
      {
        "start": 16.4,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "and use each one in a sentence."
      },
      {
        "start": 18.5,
        "duration": 4.1,
        "text": "Ingenious is an adjective that\nmeans clever or inventive."
      },
      {
        "start": 22.6,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "Having lots of smart new ideas."
      },
      {
        "start": 24.6,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "Coming up with cool\ninventions or solutions."
      },
      {
        "start": 28.0,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "Experience, it's both a noun and a verb."
      },
      {
        "start": 30.7,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "As a noun, it means something\nthat has happened to you,"
      },
      {
        "start": 33.4,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "or knowledge or skills\ngained by doing something."
      },
      {
        "start": 36.8,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "As a verb, it means to go\nthrough something yourself."
      },
      {
        "start": 40.2,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "Evaluate, it's a verb."
      },
      {
        "start": 41.4,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "It means to analyze or examine something"
      },
      {
        "start": 43.9,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "in order to form an opinion about it."
      },
      {
        "start": 46.6,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "Let's get into where\nthese words come from."
      },
      {
        "start": 48.9,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "For ingenious, let's\nfocus on two word parts."
      },
      {
        "start": 51.9,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "In means, well, in."
      },
      {
        "start": 54.0,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "And gen means born or created."
      },
      {
        "start": 57.2,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "It's the idea of skill or\nsmarts being an inborn quality,"
      },
      {
        "start": 62.1,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "something you've either got or you don't."
      },
      {
        "start": 64.5,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "For my part, I don't\nreally think that's true."
      },
      {
        "start": 66.6,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "I worked very hard to know\neverything that I know,"
      },
      {
        "start": 69.4,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "and I bet you did too."
      },
      {
        "start": 71.2,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "Word origins aren't destiny."
      },
      {
        "start": 73.3,
        "duration": 0.9,
        "text": "Just because a word has"
      },
      {
        "start": 74.2,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "a particular origin doesn't make it true."
      },
      {
        "start": 77.6,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "Something to keep in mind."
      },
      {
        "start": 79.1,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "Related words to ingenious include,"
      },
      {
        "start": 81.9,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "generate, to make, to produce."
      },
      {
        "start": 84.3,
        "duration": 3.8,
        "text": "I can generate electricity\nfrom these solar panels."
      },
      {
        "start": 88.0,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "Gene."
      },
      {
        "start": 88.9,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "A gene is a science term."
      },
      {
        "start": 90.5,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "It's part of the DNA inside your cells."
      },
      {
